title.narrative: Cities Implementing Transparent, Innovative, Effective Solutions (CITIES)

description.narrative: (Jordan): The Cities Implementing Transparent, Innovative, Effective Solutions (CITIES) activity improves the effectiveness, responsiveness, and transparency of municipal governance. CITIES increases opportunities for meaningful citizen engagement by reducing impediments to local economic development while promoting social cohesion and community resilience to ongoing change in a volatile region. Through technical assistance and material support, CITIES helps partner municipalities strengthen their internal financial and human resource management systems, enhance service delivery like solid waste management, and change the way municipalities make information available to citizens through online platforms and town hall meetings. In response to Government of Jordan requests for assistance to stimulate economic opportunities, CITIES also promotes small scale jobs creation, investment opportunities, and other drivers of economic growth at the local level. USAID partners with several ministries, all 12 governors' offices, and 33 municipalities across the Kingdom. USAID will evaluate some interventions through a quasi-experimental impact evaluation to identify and scale-up successful interventions for more widespread adoption. This activity advances ICS Mission Objective 3.2 (which.incorporates the USAID Country Development Cooperation Strategy Development.Objective 2) to strengthen democratic accountability and effective governance...... .
